ICH E6(R3) Good Clinical Practice
---------------------------------
The GCP definitional layer (cr-domain/ontology/cr-core-gcp.ttl) is an
INDEPENDENT DERIVATIVE ADAPTATION of the ICH E6(R3) Good Clinical Practice
Guideline (Step 4, adopted January 2025): its Principles, Glossary, and
Annex 1 (interventional trials). Annex 2 is not modeled in this version.

  * Attribution: the ontology is based on, and acknowledges the copyright of,
    ICH E6(R3). The original ICH E6(R3) document is copyright © ICH.
  * Changes made (clearly labeled): ICH E6(R3) concepts are reorganized into
    an OWL/SKOS structure; definitions are PARAPHRASED, never copied verbatim;
    obligations ("should/shall") are expressed as SHACL constraints rather than
    encoded text. Each derived term carries rdfs:isDefinedBy the ICH source.
  * No endorsement: this is an independent, third-party development. It is NOT
    endorsed, sponsored, or verified by ICH, and no such impression is intended.
  * No ICH logo is used anywhere in this work, documentation, or UI.

The Apache-2.0 license applies to the original ontological work (classes,
properties, axioms, shapes, and code) in this repository. The underlying
conceptual definitions in the GCP layer are derived from copyrighted ICH
material as described above.

DIA TMF Reference Model
-----------------------
The TMF artifact-type scheme (cr-domain/ontology/tmf-reference.ttl) aligns by
zone/artifact NAME to the DIA TMF Reference Model, a licensed artifact. Exact
DIA artifact numbering is to be reconciled against the licensed model; no DIA
text is reproduced here. Not endorsed or sponsored by DIA.

CDISC / external ontologies
---------------------------
CDISC standards (SDTM, ADaM, USDM) appear only as projection/view targets, not
as imported or reproduced models. External-ontology crosswalks (OAE, OBI) carry
their own provenance and verification metadata in cr-domain/crosswalks/.
